Rexnord Inc said it signed adefinitive agreement to sell its Railway Maintenance EquipmentCo subsidiary to Oak Industries Inc. Terms were withheld.    Also participating in the agreement was Banner IndustriesInc, which previously agreed to acquire Rexnord.    Railway Maintenance had 1986 sales of 16 mln dlrs.    Rexnord said the sale is part of a major program to divestseveral of its businesses representing about 200 mln dlrs innet assets. Still to be divested are the Process MachineryDivision with sales of 137 mln dlrs and Mathews Conveyer Co,with sales of 83 mln dlrs. -- Corrects mame of purchaser Reuter&#3;